// Real UC Davis course data, parsed directly from the official course catalog
// (catalog.ucdavis.edu/courses-subject-code/<code>/) for the 6 areas this app currently touches
// via the UC Davis partner-school addition (see CLAUDE.md). Deliberately scoped to these 23
// subject codes only, per the build spec's own "do not attempt the remaining 160+ subject codes"
// instruction — this is NOT a full UC Davis catalog ingestion, the same "scoped, not exhaustive"
// posture Roslyn High School's own 207-course catalog build already established.
//
// Two deliberate exclusions applied uniformly while parsing every subject code, same "don't pad
// with noise" judgment call this codebase already makes elsewhere:
// 1. Purely administrative/variable-content catch-alls (Directed Group Study, Special/Individual
//    Study, generic Internship placements, Tutoring, Research Group Conferences, Honors
//    thesis/research units, bare "Lower/Upper Division Seminar" with no stated topic) are left
//    out — these have no fixed, real description to report (the catalog itself just says
//    "variable" or "independent study"), so listing them would mean inventing content, not
//    parsing it.
// 2. Exact-duplicate delivery-mode variants (a plain course plus its "V" online / "Y" hybrid
//    twin sharing the identical title and description) are collapsed to one entry — the content
//    is the same course, not a second real course.
// Lower + Upper Division only (no 200-level graduate courses) — this data feeds an
// UNDERGRADUATE transcript-entry screen. `credit` is left as a string since UC Davis units are
// sometimes a range (e.g. "1-5"), unlike Roslyn's fixed per-course credit values.
//
// Four subject codes from the build spec's own list (ACC, BAX, HRT, ENV) turned out to have NO
// real Lower/Upper Division undergraduate courses at all when fetched — confirmed directly from
// each one's own catalog page (they're graduate-only subject codes) — so they contribute zero
// entries here rather than a guessed placeholder. This is why Business/Economics' 4 subject
// codes reduce to real coverage from just ECN + MGT, and Horticulture/Ag & Environment's 6
// reduce to ESM + ESP + SAF + PLB.

